# World Studio agentic parity

## Default agent loop

1. Read `docs/game-dev/ue-parity-agentic-roadmap.md`
2. Patch **Li** (`world.li`, packages) — not C oracles in package trees
3. `lic build` composable gates touched by the change
4. `bench.py --only <affected>` for world/gaming kernels
5. `./scripts/publish-benchmarks-ingest.sh` when timings matter

## UE comparison (required before claiming vs Unreal)

- Run `./scripts/run-ue-samples.sh` on a machine with `UE_ROOT` (not cloud-only agents)
- Or ingest manual CSV via `import_ue_baseline.py`
- Do **not** treat `unreal-proxy-targets.json` budgets as measured UE

## Parity priorities (P1)

- `sim_step_physics` Li body + `physics.runtime`
- `li-render` present path + frame bench
- Native `li-studio` shell (command palette, adaptive panels)
